This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category because it deals with deep convolutional neural networks and their applications. It also involves pruning techniques, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks to reduce computational requirements. The paper also discusses the use of importance factor matrix to adjust weight importance and weight gradients, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper proposes a new pruning method, which involves structured pruning in the spatial domain, and this technique is related to data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
